Suggests: indi-bin
Description: OpenAstro PHD2 auto-guiding with ASCOM Alpaca and INDI support
 PHD2 is a telescope auto-guiding application designed to be easy to use
 while providing powerful, intelligent guiding. Connect your mount, your
 camera, select a star, and start guiding.
 .
 This build includes integrated ASCOM Alpaca and INDI support for controlling
 cameras, mounts, and rotators over the local network.
 .
 Runs headlessly as the openastro-phd2 system user via systemd, exposing the
 PHD2 JSON-RPC API for remote control by planetarium and capture software.

Package: phd2-alpaca
Architecture: all
Section: oldlibs
Priority: optional
Depends: openastro-phd2 (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: transitional package - renamed to openastro-phd2
 OpenAstro PHD2 2.0.0 renamed the binary Debian package from phd2-alpaca
 to openastro-phd2 so it matches the macOS bundle identifier
 (net.openastro.phd2) and the Windows installer's OpenAstro branding.
 .
 This is an empty transitional metadata package that depends on
 openastro-phd2. It exists so that apt-managed upgrades from a host
 that had phd2-alpaca installed pull in openastro-phd2 automatically.
 Once the upgrade completes you can safely remove this package with
 `sudo apt remove phd2-alpaca` - no service or files are owned by it.
